  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profile**. While you can see who has viewed your Instagram Stories and Reels, the platform maintains user privacy by not disclosing profile visit information.\n\n### What You Can See on Instagram:\n\n1. **Stories and Reels Views**:\n   - **Stories**: After you post a Story, you can swipe up on the screen to see a list of users who have viewed it.\n   - **Reels**: When someone watches your Reel, you can see the number of views, but not necessarily all the individual viewers unless they interact with it (like liking or commenting).\n\n2. **Post Engagement**:\n   - You can see who has liked or commented on your posts, which indicates engagement but doesn\u2019t specifically show profile visits.\n\n### Beware of Third-Party Apps and Services\n\nSome third-party apps and websites claim to show you who has viewed your Instagram profile. **Be cautious with these services** for several reasons:\n\n- **Privacy Risks**: Granting access to your Instagram account to third-party apps can compromise your personal information and security.\n- **Violation of Instagram\u2019s Terms of Service**: Using such apps can lead to your account being restricted or banned.\n- **Scams and Malware**: Many of these services are scams designed to collect your data or install malware on your device.\n\n### Protecting Your Privacy on Instagram\n\nIf you're concerned about who can see your content or profile, consider adjusting your privacy settings:\n\n1. **Switch to a Private Account**:\n   - Go to your profile, tap the menu (three lines) in the top right, go to **Settings** > **Privacy**, and toggle on **Private Account**. This way, only approved followers can see your posts and profile details.\n\n2. **Manage Story Privacy**:\n   - In **Settings** > **Privacy** > **Story**, you can hide your story from specific users or allow replies and interactions only from certain people.\n\n3. **Review Active Sessions**:\n   - To ensure no unauthorized access to your account, go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Login Activity** and review the devices and locations where your account is logged in.\n\n### Staying Updated\n\nSocial media platforms frequently update their features and privacy policies. To stay informed about any changes related to profile view features:\n\n- **Check Instagram\u2019s Official Help Center**: [Instagram Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/)\n- **Follow Official Instagram Channels** for updates and announcements.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nCurrently, there's no legitimate way to see who has viewed your Instagram profile. Rely on the built-in features provided by Instagram for insights and interactions, and always prioritize your account's security by avoiding untrustworthy third-party apps.",
